tag.description: The palms already appeared in the background of many photographs taken during the first National Day Parade held at the Padang in 1966.

Bears its flowers and fruits on thick long stalks that grow directly from the tree trunk. The large, fleshy flowers are attractive and fragrant. Its fruits are round and hard, resembling cannon balls, hence its common name.
Brazilian Ironwood (Libidibia ferrea) originates from tropical America. It can grow up to 20 m. The bark patches resemble a leopard's hide, hence the other common name, Leopard Tree.
Also called Jejawi. Native to India, South China, Indochina, Malaysia, Polynesia, tropical Australia.

This tree has been standing here for more than 70 years, and was endorsed as a Heritage Tree in 2008. The Tamarind is a slow growing tree that is widely cultivated for its sweet-sourish fruit pulp known as "asam".

tag.description: The species is native to tropical America, and this particular cultivar can grow up to 12 m tall. It produces large white flowers with a yellow centre and waxy petals that form a funnel.
The Champaca tree is often planted around Hindu temples. Their flowers, bright orange or yellow, give off a strong fragrance.
Teak is a termite resistant species and therefore its wood is used in construction and for outdoor furniture.
